acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

params._amount: the amount of tokens to send
params._to: the address to send the tokens to

revokeApprovals(address[],address).details: only available for the owner. Can't revoke the approvals from the current minting contract

params._target: address to revoke the approvals from

setMintingContract(address).details: only available for the owner, high probability that this function never gets called

setOperator(address).details: only available for the owner. We allow the address(0) as a new operator in case that the key is exposed and we just want to remove the current operator as soon as possible being able to set to 0

transferInRewards(uint256).details: In order to use this function, we need to set this contract as the REWARDER_ROLE in the staking contract      No need to check that the input amount is not 0, since we already check this in the staking contract

params._rewardsAmount: the amount of USDe to send

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

approveToMintContract(address[]).notice: approves the desired assets to the minting contract

operator().notice: only address authorized to invoke transferInRewards

renounceOwnership().notice: prevents the owner from renouncing the owner role

rescueTokens(address,address,uint256).notice: owner can rescue tokens that were accidentally sent to the contract

revokeApprovals(address[],address).notice: revokes the previously granted ERC20 approvals from a specific address

setOperator(address).notice: sets a new operator and delegated signer, removing the previous one

transferInRewards(uint256).notice: only the operator can call transferInRewards in order to transfer USDe to the staking contract
